    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 1 against a required level 2 due to single test configuration; this gap is documented and accepted given the well-characterized ASTM F1717 protocol and the medium model risk classification. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use. Re-validation of model inputs against the February 2026 model revision is planned for Q2 2026.",
